  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is a red chalk drawing by Hendrick Goltzius (1558–1617), depicting the famous equestrian statue of Marcus Aurelius on the Capitoline Hill in Rome. It was made during Goltzius' transformative Italian journey of 1590–1591. The drawing is one of approximately 125 Goltzius sheets held by Teylers Museum — the largest collection of Goltzius drawings in the world. It was acquired in 1790 from the Odescalchi heirs in Rome, as part of a purchase of approximately 1,700 drawings that had passed through the collection of Queen Christina of Sweden.",
